      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles derived from Coriolis-meter measurements (±0.5%). Blood viscosity from rheometry on test fluid lot (±3.1%). Power-law hemolysis model constants (C = 1.8×10⁻⁶, α = 1.991, β = 0.765) taken from Giersiepen et al. and confirmed against Heuser & Opitz. All inputs documented in simulation log. The primary experimental dataset used to anchor boundary condition fidelity carries dataVintage 2025-08-22; this predates the model revision of 2025-09-15 by 24 days. The turbulence closure coefficient adjustment made at revision was assessed informally as not affecting inlet-condition mapping, but no re-validation run was executed against post-revision inputs."
